    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.3.33-34"/>
                <note type="curatorial">33</note>
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="authorial">
                    150 ROOMS 
                    LIGHT SAMPLE ROOMS 
                    ABSOLUTELY 
                    FIRE PROOF 
                    Hotel <figure/> HM Magnus 
                    W.L.YANCEY, PROP.
                    MART.F.GREAGER, RESIDENT MANAGER
                    CEDAR RAPIDS, IOWA, 
                </fw>
                <opener>
                    
                    <dateline>
                        Oct 6. [1922]
                    </dateline> 
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mama:-</salute>
                </opener>
                
                <p>My other letter to all of you tells some things about Lulu, but I forgot to tell
                    about her studying the art of movie-writing. She is taking a course with the
                    Palmer school of Los Angeles in scenario-writing, &amp; is doing well. She hopes
                    to be able to make something to help Donald out. They still owe $900 on their
                    place &amp; it's a dickens of a grind to keep up there.</p> 
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.3.33-34"/>
                <note type="curatorial">34</note>
                <note type="authorial">-2-</note>
                
                <p>establishment. I really believe Lulu may make a go of it. She has had some reason to be encouraged. donald <unclear/> her about it, but so glad just the same. Lulu says that, from the first, she has thought of trying to but "Three Friends" across in teh movies. Wouldn't it be bully if we could be <unclear/> in this way!</p> 
                <p>I hope your carnival will work out big, &amp; I think it will. I told Lulu all
                    about your activities &amp; she was greatly interested, of course. Lots of love, Mama.</p> 
                <signed>Jno</signed> 
            </div1>
        </body>
        
